-- Zimbabwe Bank Deposits Rise to $4 Billion, Newsday Reports
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-05-28T09:05:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-28/zimbabwe-bank-deposits-rise-to-4-billion-newsday-reports.html
Bank deposits in  Zimbabwe  rose to $4
billion this month from $3.3 billion in January,  Newsday  said,
citing central bank Governor Gideon Gono.  Loans amounted to $2.8 billion, Harare-based Newsday said
on its website. Only 5 percent of credit went to small and
medium-sized businesses, Newsday cited Gono as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 